# URL of the Defend the Crystal multiplayer server (Socket.IO / Render).
#
# Leave BLANK for local dev — the client then defaults to
# http://<current-host>:3001, which matches `npm run dev:server`.
#
# In production, set this on Vercel per environment:
#   - Production  -> your Render production URL   (e.g. https://dtc-server.onrender.com)
#   - Preview     -> a stable Render URL (usually the same production/main server)
#
# You can always override it at runtime with ?server=<url> in the page URL —
# handy to point a Vercel preview at a Render PR-preview server.
VITE_SERVER_URL=
